;s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(6987,264,'preview_image','336'),(6988,264,'_preview_image','field_596cd093b14d0'),(6989,264,'background_image','350'),(6990,264,'_background_image','field_59678cbb3d349'),(6991,264,'short_description','This Italian peasant-style salad is all about having the right bread, the juiciest tomatoes, the ripest peppers and the freshest basil. Add in a bit of good olive oil and vinegar to these summer flavors for a simple, rustic dish that will impress any dinner guest.'),(6992,264,'_short_description','field_59678c333d345'),(6993,264,'directions','<ol>\r\n 	<li>With a fork, mash the garlic, anchovies and capers to a puree on a chopping board. Place in the bottom of a salad bowl.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the diced pepper and red onion to the anchovy puree. Stir in the olive oil and vinegar. Cover and chill for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Place the toasted bread squares in a separate bowl. Mash half of the diced tomatoes and mix through the bread. Let sit for 15 minutes to allow the bread to soak up the juices.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the remaining diced tomatoes and cucumber to the peppers and anchovy mixture. Stir in the soaked bread and shredded basil. Taste and season with salt and pepper.</li>\r\n 	<li>Serve with green salad and grilled or grilled meat.</li>\r\n</ol>'),(6994,264,'_directions','field_59678c403d346'),(6995,264,'ingredients','12'),(6996,264,'_ingredients','field_59678c4c3d347'),(6997,266,'_edit_last','2'),(6998,266,'_edit_lock','1508986798:2'),(6999,267,'_wp_attached_file','2017/07/turkey-cheese-and-red-onion-sandwich.jpg'),(7000,267,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:1272;s:6:\"height\";i:716;s:4:\"file\";s:48:\"2017/07/turkey-cheese-and-red-onion-sandwich.jpg\";s:5:\"s